    <stitle>FRONT STEER AXLE: EATON EFA-12 - REMOVE/DISASSEMBLE - STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl0200603" svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>STEERING KNUCKLE DISASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Back off slack adjuster to return brake shoes to the released position and clear of drum.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove hub cap from wheel, then remove cotter pin, nut, washer, and outer bearing cone
                assembly.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove wheel and hub assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect air (or hydraulic) line from the brake assembly.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not allow contamination of hydraulic fluid.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove brake assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To disconnect tie rod end from Ackermann Arm, remove cotter pin and slotted nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200604">Figure 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200604" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200604.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 4. Remove Cotter Pin and Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect tie rod end using suitable tool (pickle fork, see
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0200605">Figure 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f0200605" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg02/G0200605.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 5. Disconnect Tie Rod End</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use heat on any parts or fasteners.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Disconnect drag link from steering arm by removing cotter pin and slotted nut.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>For more information on disconnecting tie rod ends, refer to GROUP 02 - FRONT AXLES in the CTS-5000 Master
            Service Manual.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
